<div type="edition" xml:lang="tel-Latn" rendition="class:telugu maturity:vernacular">

<p>
<lb n="1"/>svasti <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> śrī śakavaruṣaṁbulu
<lb n="2"/>1310 Agunēṁṭi vibhava
<lb n="3"/>bhādrapada śu 5 śu śrībhāva
<lb n="4" break="no"/>nārāyaṇaperumā<unclear>ḷa</unclear>
<lb n="5" break="no"/>ku kāṭamareḍi<unclear>pe</unclear>tta<unclear>ya</unclear>reḍi<note n="3-2">From what follows in 1. 13 f. it looks as if the reading Pettayareḍi in this line stands for Vēmireḍi.</note>
<lb n="6"/>dattaṁ cōḍasamudraṁ tūrpuna
<lb n="7"/>biṁdāvanamuku cēnu yaṭi
<lb n="8" break="no"/>kālaceṟuvu paḍumaṭi pola
<lb n="9" break="no"/>mukha 2 ku krayamugānu na
<lb n="10" break="no"/>gariki celliṁcina ṭaṁkālu ṭa 40 [<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g>]
<lb n="11"/>[Ī] nalupai ṭaṁkālu śrīśrī
<lb n="12"/>sarpavaraṁ bhāvayyaku peṭi
<lb n="13"/>Ā vēmireḍiṁgāru krayaṁgo
<lb n="14" break="no"/>nna cēnu kha 2 nu tama taṁḍrikā
<lb n="15" break="no"/>ṭamareḍiṁgāriki tama talli do
<lb n="16" break="no"/>ḍāsānammaṁgāriki puṇyaṁgā
<lb n="17" break="no"/>ṁ beṭiṁcina Iṭika nūṟa puvu
<lb n="18" break="no"/>ṁdōṁṭa na 4 kṣētrānā sakala pu
<lb n="19" break="no"/>se puṣpajātulupeṭi Ā
<lb n="20" break="no"/>caṁdrārkkaṁgā śrībhāvadē
<lb n="21" break="no"/>varaku trikālamu pu
<lb n="22" break="no"/><unclear>va</unclear>la tōmālalu peṭivā
<lb n="23" break="no"/>ri jītāna kistimi <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> 
</p>

